(2790, 0, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/Dl7jWegLC8w/'' title=''WordPress 3.4 Beta 2 has been released. Since the first beta, there have been over 60 bug fixes and adjustments based on testing a feedback. As before, this is not yet meant for live sites, but please do take a few swings at it on a test installation, especially if you are a plugin or theme developer. If you find any bugs, please report them, and contact the [&hellip;]''>Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress 3.4 Beta 2 Released</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2012/04/php-is-crazy/'' title=''I loved this comment on Hacker News, especially the last paragraph which I’ll quote here: The question implicit in your comment is: Could we design a system that offers the ease of accessibility of the first few steps of a PHP programmer’s career but, as one climbs the learning curve, eventually blossoms into Python or Ruby or even Lisp? I wish I knew. My be [&hellip;]''>Matt: PHP is crazy</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.org/news/2012/04/wordpress-3-4-beta-2/'' title=''Howdy, folks! Another week, another beta. Since we released Beta 1 last week, we’ve committed more than 60 bug fixes and feature adjustments based on testing and feedback. If you’ve been testing Beta 1, please update to Beta 2 to make sure things are still working for you. If you are a theme or plugin author and have not yet started testing your code against [&hellip;]''>Dev Blog: WordPress 3.4 Beta 2</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2012/04/wordpress-and-the-top-100/'' title=''Pingdom writes WordPress completely dominates top 100 blogs. I’m quoted in the article saying that the 49% marketshare we have among top blogs will continue to grow, and I’d like to expand on that a bit because it’s a strong statement. Typepad and Blogsmith, the two platforms that dropped the most over the past 3 years, are going to disappear either through  [&hellip;]''>Matt: WordPress and the Top 100</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/-TTk7btYNps/'' title=''New plugins Sharexy is a powerful social sharing, bookmarking, and blog monetization tool. WP Social Feedback allows your users to submit feedback, view what other users have submitted and vote on other feedback submissions. WP Visited Countries allows you to easily create and publish a map of the countries you have visited and lived in. Updated plugins Bulk [&hellip;]''>Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Plugin Releases for 4/11</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
