(2648, 0, 'tax_meta_121', 'a:2:{s:12:"author_image";a:2:{s:2:"id";s:3:"494";s:3:"src";s:103:"http://digital.lampdev.columbia.edu/morningsidereview/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/1-DSC_1118-300x198.jpg";}s:10:"author_bio";s:467:"<p>Ben Ilany is from Scarsdale, New York, and will be graduating from<br />\nColumbia\\''s School of General Studies in spring 2012 with a major in Middle<br />\nEastern, South Asian, and African Studies. While serving in Mosul, Iraq a<br />\nfriend told him that Columbia was a friendly place for veterans, so he spent<br />\nhis nights writing my admissions essay. He loves traveling around the world,<br />\nSCUBA diving, and writing about his experiences. hit here.</p>\n";}', 'yes'),
(2653, 0, 'tax_meta_122', 'a:1:{s:10:"author_bio";s:249:"<p>Abigail Golden is a sophomore in Columbia College double majoring in<br />\nEnglish and environmental biology. She was born and raised in Brooklyn<br />\nbut, despite her upbringing in the concrete jungle, enjoys hiking and<br />\nthe outdoors.</p>\n";}', 'yes'),
(2655, 0, 'tax_meta_123', 'a:2:{s:12:"author_image";a:2:{s:2:"id";s:3:"495";s:3:"src";s:105:"http://digital.lampdev.columbia.edu/morningsidereview/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/rene_moraida-225x300.jpg";}s:10:"author_bio";s:701:"<p>Rene Moraida is a senior at Columbia University’s School of General Studies majoring in Political Science. After graduating in May 2012, Rene will attend graduate school at the University of California San Diego’s School of International Relations and Pacific Studies. A native of Corpus Christi, Texas, Rene enjoys catching up on national and international news, watching cooking and travel shows, dining out in Brooklyn or Chelsea, and trying to find some quiet time in this chaotic metropolis. Rene loves seeing new places, learning new languages, and experiencing different cultures. He hopes to serve in the Peace Corps and eventually become a diplomat with the U.S. State Department.</p>\n";}', 'yes'),
(2659, 0, 'tax_meta_124', 'a:1:{s:10:"author_bio";s:219:"<p>Spencer Cunningham is from Cary, North Carolina and is a sophomore in Columbia College.  He is an avid writer and musician and enjoys surfing, cooking, and the occasional N64 game when he’s feeling nostalgic.</p>\n";}', 'yes'),
(2662, 0, 'tax_meta_125', 'a:2:{s:12:"author_image";a:2:{s:2:"id";s:3:"496";s:3:"src";s:106:"http://digital.lampdev.columbia.edu/morningsidereview/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/blair_pfander-300x225.jpg";}s:10:"author_bio";s:290:"<p>Blair Pfander is a General Studies student majoring in creative writing. When she\\''s not interviewing young designers or editing video for her day job as a fashion blogger, she\\''s Googling Mark Bittman recipes (current obsession: \\"no-knead\\" bread) or Michael Jordan\\''s slam dunks.</p>\n";}', 'yes'),
(2666, 0, 'tax_meta_126', 'a:2:{s:12:"author_image";a:2:{s:2:"id";s:3:"497";s:3:"src";s:95:"http://digital.lampdev.columbia.edu/morningsidereview/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/mica_moore.jpg";}s:10:"author_bio";s:489:"<p>Mica Moore is a student in Columbia College, double majoring in Political Science and English and Comparative Literature.  Growing up in the Washington DC region, Mica has held a lifelong interest in politics. She is also interested in the relationship of literature to broader political movements, particularly in 19<sup>th</sup> century Russian literature. Mica has contributed to the Columbia Spectator and the Columbia Review. In her spare time, she enjoys exploring New York.</p>\n";}', 'yes'),
