r subject is a singular, identifiable entity. Her portraits of women are multidimensional in themselves, presented in the context of hundreds of other women with diverse backgrounds and experiences. Her subject is women as a category that defies categorization. v\n\n&nbsp;', 'What is She Up To?: Annie Leibovitz and the Politics of Representation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '218-autosave', '', '', '2012-02-28 10:25:57', '2012-02-28 10:25:57', '', 218, 'http://digital.lampdev.columbia.edu/morningsidereview/?p=219', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
